<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1233,1259]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1436,1233,1377]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">The genus can be recognized by the following characters: medium-sized; vertex transverse, median carina sometimes weak; frons wide, with median carina, sublateral carinae distinct only in upper half; tegmen with hypocostal plate; Sc short and fusing with R forming a loop; hind wing well three-lobed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
